post_text:
***Updated information for Homecoming next week.*** Please note that outdoor activities will be pending weather. The public is welcome to attend the kickoff at the football field beginning at 6:00 on Sunday. We encourage social distancing.

The Homecoming Kickoff on Sunday will include: class games (non-contact), announcement of the homecoming court, senior dance team boy/girl dance, and the football jersey auction. Math Club will also have snacks/refreshments available. Prior to the kick-off, high school students will be painting windows downtown. High school students will receive additional details at class meetings that will be held on Friday afternoon.

Let's make this a great Homecoming 2020! #mvpride
(poster design cred to MVHS student, Jaden Lasater)

post_text:
Good evening!

Apparently the delivery company had it wrong and our new picnic tables arrived late this afternoon! While we apologize for the late notice, we are thrilled that we will get to expand our outdoor seating opportunities for our students.

Therefore, to make sure this round is ready for students next week, we will look to assemble them (14 tables) this Sunday at 12:00pm in the Middle School Circle. Any and all help would be appreciated!

Please bring tools (1/2 in socket, driller/driver, wrench, etc...) if you have them.

Thank you so much for your continued support of Missouri Valley Schools and our students!!

What: Picnic Table assembly
Where: Missouri Valley Middle School Parking Lot
When: Sunday, August 16 @ 12:00pm

*Many hands make light work!

post_text:
The first day of school is quickly approaching! In accordance with our Return to Learn Plan, there will NOT be a traditional Open House this week. Each building (elementary, middle, and high) will be sending out a Virtual Open House on Wednesday, August 12th.

We understand that students have a lot of supplies and some won't fit in their backpacks! We recommend that students bring only the essential supplies (pencils, notebooks, folders, markers, crayons, scissors, and glue) on the first day of school! Bring the rest the following week! This applies to all students PK-12th grade! #mvpride

We truly have an amazing community!!

Missouri Valley High School is seeking an outstanding High School English/Language Arts teacher. Desired certifications: Language Arts - All, Journalism.

HEY LADY REDS!

Camp starts tomorrow bright and early. Please look at previous post for specifics about camp.

A few reminders:
- Grades 3-5 @ 8:30 - 10:00
- Grades 6-8 @ 10:30 - 12:30
- Grades 9-12 @ 1:30 - 3:30

*Masks are optional for the players to wear, they are not required for camp.
*Each player needs to bring their own water bottle for water breaks
*If possible, each player needs to bring hand sanitizer, as we will be taking breaks throughout camp to sanitize
*When registering at the door, each player will be asked to write down an emergency contact name and number
*Each player will receive a camp t-shirt as soon as they are registered!

So excited to see you all this week and play some volleyball! ğŸ˜€

Camp starts tomorrow bright and early. Please look at previous post for specifics about camp.

A few reminders:
- Grades 3-5 @ 8:30 - 10:00
- Grades 6-8 @ 10:30 - 12:30
- Grades 9-12 @ 1:30 - 3:30

*Masks are optional for the players to wear, they are not required for camp.
*Each player needs to bring their own water bottle for water breaks
*If possible, each player needs to bring hand sanitizer, as we will be taking breaks throughout camp to sanitize
*When registering at the door, each player will be asked to write down an emergency contact name and number
*Each player will receive a camp t-shirt as soon as they are registered!

So excited to see you all this week and play some volleyball! ğŸ˜€

post_text:
Middle School Training Camp is a morning designed to help incoming 6th-grade students. Training Camp is a fun way for Big Reds/Lady Reds to learn and adjust to middle school. The program focuses on expectations in middle school and understanding schedules and daily routines.
Students learn how to effectively move from class to class, and they are given an extensive tour of the building. We hope that you can join us for a morning of learning and fun! Training camp will be held on August 10th! We will be providing three separate training camp options for students this year based on the student's last names. Last names A-G will attend from 8:30 to 9:30, H-P 10:00 to 11:00, and Q-Z will attend from 11:30 to 12:30. Please, bring a facemask that will cover your student's nose and mouth. If your student does not have a mask one will be provided to them that day. Look for more information coming soon on Infinite Campus. We look forward to meeting you! #MVPride

post_text: Reminder for the Class of 2020 graduates and their families! #mvpride
shared_text:
Risney Photo & Design, INC. is with Kristie Kruckman and 3 others.
May 30 at 6:28 PM Â·

Two weeks ago on a cold, blustery, rainy day, I photographed the Class of 2020 in Missouri Valley for their graduation ceremony. We made the best of it in the rain and the photos actually turned out really well. MV graduates, if you haven't seen yours and want to purchase it, you need to contact the HIGH SCHOOL as I was hired by the school to do this for you and then you need to contact the school to purchase it. It's not how we usually do things for graduation, but then again NOTHING this year has been like we do it! "Normal" kind of went out the window! Congratulations to you all. It's been great photographing many of you in the different sports through the years. Take care and have a wonderful life!

It's Officially Summer!

Thank you all the parents, staff, and others who have helped our students throughout the last 10 weeks with their at-home studies. Thank you students for continuing to participate in online meetings, watching instructional videos, working through online applications and resources, and completing paper packet assignments in order to be more prepared for the future!

Congratulations Class of 2020! This year was nothing like you thought it would be and you handled all the diversity with grace. You are going to do amazing things in this world!

We look forward to the fall when, hopefully, we will be able to resume class in person! Have a safe and fun summer!

With Big Reds' Pride!

Dr. Hoesing

Happy last day of school, MV students and families! We did it! As Robert Frost says, "The only way out is through." We appreciate your patience, your collaboration, and your continued support of MVCSD during school closure.

Please see the latest route for our 2020 graduate parade! The event will take place on Sunday, May 17 at approximately 4:30 pm.

Families and community members are encouraged to participate in cheering on our grads along the proposed route as long as they follow CDC guidelines:
~Maintain social distancing (stay 6 feet, or about 2 armsâ€™ length) from other people.
~Do not gather in large groups or block sidewalks. Spread out along the route and away from others that are not in your same household.
~Wear a cloth face cover.
~If you do not feel well, please stay home.
~If you have been around someone who has tested positive for COVID-19, please do not attend the event.
~Another option; remain in your car, parked along the street

We hope to see you at the event to congratulate our graduates!

The 6th grade teachers took â€œZoomâ€ to the next level! This week, as part of a 6th grade assignment, students were asked to respond to Mrs. Vosterâ€™s Google Classroom question, â€œWould you like a visit from your teachers?â€ On Wednesday and Friday, Mrs. Guinan, Mrs. Voster, and Mr. Cihacek traveled from Modale to Cal Junction, to Missouri Valley and surprised their students with snacks and a socially distant face-to-face check in! A couple of students even shot hoops with Mr. C!

All three teachers agreed that â€œIt was so nice to see our kids. We miss them all so much. With only a couple of weeks left of â€œschoolâ€, we figured it was a good time to get out and talk with them one-on-one. We think they all enjoyed it too!â€ #mvpride

post_text:
Missouri Valley Parents/Guardians,

With school cancelled for the year, Missouri Valley Schools is looking to see what we can do to support our community during this time. We would like to know if we have essential workers in the community who are in need of daycare. If there is enough interest, school will consider re-opening the Wrap-Around services to help provide for these essential workers. These services would be available for students who attend Missouri Valley Schools, Preschool - 5th Grade.

If you are interested and need daycare during this time, and are interested in the school-provided services, please complete the survey below by Friday, April 24.

If the Wrap-Around reopens, it will do so at the High School so we are better able to stay in compliance with DHS COVID-19 guidelines and mitigation practices. More details are included within the survey and DHS guidance can be found here: https://dhs.iowa.gov/childcare-covid-19

https://forms.gle/mgF6PV8bw8gPPhZQA

post_text:
Each week for the past 18 months, staff at MVCSD have been receiving a weekly dose of self-care in their email inbox. Our weekly emails, "Take Care of Yourself Tuesday", provide our staff with a reminder to practice self-care.

Due to the current situation, we thought it was important for parents, students, and community members to also be encouraged to practice self-care in their daily lives during this unprecedented time. #mvpride

Clipart: Carrie Stephens Art (TheCounselingTeacher.com)
text:
Each week for the past 18 months, staff at MVCSD have been receiving a weekly dose of self-care in their email inbox. Our weekly emails, "Take Care of Yourself Tuesday", provide our staff with a reminder to practice self-care.

post_text:
In science, Mrs. Chambersâ€™ class has been working with the engineering design process. First, they asked a question "Can foil boats float?" Then, they imagined what a foil boat would look like. Students planned and designed their boat on a piece of paper and used that paper to create their actual model with foil. Once the boats were made, they were tested. All the boats floated!

The next process was to see whose boat would hold the most pennies. Students had to take their boat and make improvements if needed, to hopefully hold the most pennies. They had a blast creating the boats and testing them! #mvpride

Engineering Design Process
1. Ask a question/solve a problem
2. Imagine how to solve it
3. Plan out your design
4. Create and Test
5. Make Improvements

post_text: The Career Transitions class toured an apartment in Missouri Valley on Friday to practice interacting with a potential landlord. Each student had two questions prepared to ask the landlord and enjoyed looking at the apartment. Trista McLaughlin, landlord, shared lots of insight with the students as to what to look for when looking at an apartment and provided a copy of a lease agreement, which the class will review in detail next week during their class time. We are happy they got to experience a real-life scenario as they are preparing for future independence! #mvpride #careerready #collegeready #lifeready

post_text:
Mrs. Cihacek's high school Health classes have been learning about fat and sugar content in foods and drinks. They did an experiment in class today in which they had to figure the total grams of sugar or fat in the product and then transfer it into teaspoons. They used actual sugar to represent the amount of sugar in the drinks and some of the foods. They used Crisco shortening to represent the amount of fat in some foods.

The results were pretty shocking to see and hopefully will make it easier for students to choose healthier options!

post_text: MVSCSD continues to address vaping issues. This is an example of the battle that we face on a daily basis. With very little signs off use, vaping devices get more and more difficult to detect in our schools. Encouraging students to report use, educating students about risky choices, and gaining the support of our school families and community is the only way we can change the culture of acceptance. Let's work together to keep our students safe and promote a safe and healthy environment for all students! #mvpride
shared_text:
MVC4C - Missouri Valley Coalition 4 Change
March 5 at 5:03 PM Â·

Can you tell which one of these is a pen and which one is a vape? Vaping products are getting more and more difficult to identify. This was shared by a local parent who confiscated these from a child who was visiting their home. Yes! This is from right here in Missouri Valley! Stay informed, stay involved, stay educated, and speak with your child about the dangers of vaping. With a rising population off underaging vapers, no one is immune! #takeastance #talktoyourchild #parentsmatter

Encouraging students to report use, educating students about risky choices, and gaining the support of our school families and community is the only way we can change the culture of acceptance. Let's work together to keep our students safe and promote a safe and healthy environment for all students! #mvpride

MVC4C - Missouri Valley Coalition 4 Change
March 5 at 5:03 PM Â·

Can you tell which one of these is a pen and which one is a vape? Vaping products are getting more and more difficult to identify. This was shared by a local parent who confiscated these from a child who was visiting their home. Yes! This is from right here in Missouri Valley! Stay informed, stay involved, stay educated, and speak with your child about the dangers of vaping. With a rising population off underaging vapers, no one is immune! #takeastance #talktoyourchild #parentsmatter

post_text:
Ms. Blazek's Intensive Algebra class used the Kagan Cooperative Learning Structure, Showdown, while working on equivalent fractions this week!

The Showdown Captain drew a fraction from the stack of cards, then everyone had to write an equivalent fraction. The fun part is learning that equivalent fractions can be either bigger OR smaller than the starting fraction. A lot of times, students only think about reducing fractions using division, but equivalent fractions can be multiplied also. #mvpride

post_text: This week's CTE (Career and Tech Education) spotlight is on Family and Consumer Science. Mrs. Regina Rains is the FCS instruct and has been teaching at MVHS for the last six years. FCS classes that students can take include, Basic Nutrition & Food Prep, Food for Life, Culinary Arts, Child Development, Intro. to FCS, and Fashion/Interior Design. She also is the Family, Career and Community Leaders of America (FCCLA) advisor. Missouri Valley High School senior, Andrew Murray, had this to say about his experiences in the FCS program: "These classes have helped me develop my love and passion for cooking food and serving food to others. The Missouri Valley High School FCS Department has given me basic sanitation information to go into the Culinary Arts program with background information, allowing me to do well in my safety and sanitation class and helping me pass the National Restaurant Association Serv Safe test."

Mrs. Ganzhorn has a room full of writers! First grade students were asked to write a piece about a â€œwishâ€ that they had. Throughout the writing process, they were taught about grade level appropriate punctuation, sentence structure, spelling, and capitalization.ï¿¼ï¿¼ï¿¼ï¿¼

Note: Our young writers are encouraged to spell words they do not know using invented spelling (writing words based on the sounds that they hear in the ï¿¼ unknown word). ï¿¼ï¿¼ï¿¼Invented spelling allows children to communicate in writing long before they are ready to spell each word correctly. Another benefit is that children can express their ideas quickly and smoothly in a first draft, without being bogged down by trying to spell each word correctly.
